# Language: plans/responses vs code

## Plans and model responses

- **Plans**, explanations, solution descriptions, and any text in replies to the user — **in Russian**.
- Questions to the user, hints, and summaries — also in Russian.

## Code and comments in code

- **Source code** (variable, function, and class names; string literals in code) — **in English**.
- **Comments in code** — in English.
- Log messages and user-facing strings in the UI (when localization is not required) — may be in English; if the project already uses Russian strings or localization, follow existing practice.

## Examples

**Model response (Russian):**  
«Добавлю валидацию: проверю длину имени и наличие обязательных полей.»

**In code (English):**
```ts
// Validate name length and required fields before submit
const isValid = name.length >= 2 && requiredFields.every(Boolean);
```
